REPLASTIC INNOVATIONS: TRANSFORMING PLASTIC WASTE INTO SUSTAINABLE AND ECO-FRIENDLY SOLUTIONS
Project Overview
Replastic Innovations is a smart plastic waste management and recycling system designed to reduce plastic pollution and promote environmental sustainability using modern technologies.
This system helps manage the entire lifecycle of plastic waste, including collection, sorting, recycling, and production of reusable products. It allows organizations to efficiently track plastic waste, monitor recycling processes, and analyze environmental impact through data analytics.
The main goal of this project is to encourage responsible plastic waste management while creating eco-friendly products from recycled materials. The platform focuses on automation, sustainability, and efficient waste tracking to support a cleaner and greener future.
Features
Waste Collection Management
This feature allows the system to store and manage details of plastic waste collected from different locations such as households, industries, and public collection centers. It helps track the quantity and type of plastic waste collected.
Plastic Sorting & Processing
After collection, plastic waste is categorized based on its type and quality. The system monitors the sorting process and tracks the recycling stages to ensure proper waste management.
Recycled Product Management
The recycled plastic materials are used to manufacture useful products such as eco-bricks, tiles, containers, and other reusable materials. The system manages product details and production records.
Waste Tracking System
This feature helps track the movement of plastic waste from collection to recycling and product manufacturing. It ensures transparency and efficient monitoring of waste processing.
Billing System
The billing system generates invoices for recycling services, manages payments, and records financial transactions related to plastic collection and recycling activities.
Dashboard
The dashboard provides visual reports and analytics showing the amount of plastic recycled, products manufactured, and the environmental impact. It helps administrators make better decisions using data insights.
Technologies Used
Salesforce CRM
Salesforce CRM is used to manage data related to waste collection, recycling processes, and product management. It helps organize information efficiently and supports automation.
Flow Builder
Salesforce Flow Builder is used to automate workflows within the system. For example, it can automatically update waste collection records or notify administrators about recycling activities.
Apex Trigger
Apex triggers are used to automate specific actions in the system when certain events occur, such as updating waste records or generating alerts.
Modules
Admin Module
The admin module manages the entire system. Administrators can monitor waste collection, recycling processes, user activities, and system reports.
Waste Collection Module
This module records details about plastic waste collected from different locations and manages transportation of waste to recycling centers.
Recycling Module
The recycling module tracks the processing of plastic waste and manages recycling activities to convert waste into reusable materials.
Product Management Module
This module manages products created from recycled plastic, including product details, production quantity, and inventory management.
Payment Module
The payment module handles billing, payment tracking, and financial transactions related to recycling services.
Analytics Module
The analytics module generates reports and visual dashboards showing recycling statistics, waste reduction levels, and environmental impact.

